Contributing your own functions

Please use git to make any changes to the code. To do this, please do the following: 1. Download a copy of the repository 1. Create a new branch, ideally using a name that describes the change you intend to make. 1. Create a merge request, providing the details of the changes you have made and the purpose of the change. 1. The project owner will review and accept as s/he sees fit. This is the owners prerogative. There may be requests for further explanations or changes.
